      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:19:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " مَا مِنْ دَاءٍ إِلَّا وَ هُوَ سَارِعٌ إِلَى الْجَسَدِ يَنْتَظِرُ مَتَى يُؤْمَرُ بِهِ فَيَأْخُذَهُ وَ فِي رِوَايَةٍ أُخْرَى إِلَّا الْحُمَّى فَإِنَّهَا تَرِدُ وُرُوداً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473157\">H 14501</a> – From him, from Ahmad, from Ibn Fazzaal, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Abu Ayyub, who has said:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is none from the illnesses, but it waits, prior to rushing to the body (infecting), until after getting orders to act upon it’. And in another report: ‘Except for the fever, for it starts working as it comes’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "53. From him, from Ahmad, from Ibn Fazzaal, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Abu Ayyub, who has said: Abu Abdullah (a.s.) said: ‘There is none from the illnesses, but it waits, prior to rushing to the body (infecting), until after getting orders to act upon it’. And in another report: ‘Except for the fever, for it starts working as it comes’."
        ]
      }
    }
